WEBVTT

00:01.586 --> 00:03.922
<i>We left the shootout
at the storage facility</i>

00:03.963 --> 00:05.298
<i>and headed to our meet-up.</i>

00:05.632 --> 00:08.176
<i>A parking garage at the Mohegan Sun Casino.</i>

00:13.640 --> 00:16.684
<i>I knew Pete wouldn't be there,
and I wanted to get Reggie to a hospital</i>

00:16.809 --> 00:19.479
<i>but he said we had to hide the money first.</i>

00:20.647 --> 00:21.689
Check the crates.

00:22.524 --> 00:24.526
- What am I looking for?
- I don't know.

00:24.901 --> 00:26.236
Something big and empty.

00:41.834 --> 00:42.794
What is that?

00:53.721 --> 00:54.597
It's hollow.

00:54.639 --> 00:56.641
<i>Wait, wait, wait...</i>

00:56.933 --> 01:03.439
You put $11 million inside fucking buffalo?

01:04.274 --> 01:05.775
It was the only thing big enough.

01:09.654 --> 01:10.530
A buffalo?

01:11.155 --> 01:13.116
A catasroph... wha...

01:13.157 --> 01:16.452
What the fuck was buffalo even doing there?

01:17.203 --> 01:18.288
It's an Indian casino.

01:19.539 --> 01:24.002
I know it's fucking Indian casino.

01:25.503 --> 01:31.593
Why was fucking buffalo
in fucking parking garage?

01:32.343 --> 01:33.511
I don't know.

01:34.679 --> 01:36.681
They have a museum.
Maybe they wanted--

01:36.723 --> 01:40.685
What are you, a Mohegan Sun expert now?
You join players' club?

01:44.564 --> 01:46.649
Your boyfriend,
he no tell me nothing like this

01:47.150 --> 01:50.570
which is something, because way I ask

01:51.446 --> 01:53.990
people always talk.

01:57.827 --> 01:59.537
Why wasn't the money in a safe?

02:08.212 --> 02:11.466
I have fucking Feds up my ass.

02:11.674 --> 02:14.427
Warrant for this, warrant for that.

02:14.469 --> 02:16.929
I think to myself, "Oh, what do I do?"

02:17.055 --> 02:19.474
I take the money,
and I put it in fucking locker

02:19.515 --> 02:20.975
where people leave shit behind.

02:21.017 --> 02:22.185
No one look there.

02:22.435 --> 02:23.519
Smart, huh?

02:23.561 --> 02:29.859
Because two days later,
Feds come in this place, rip shit apart!

02:30.276 --> 02:32.695
Tore out fucking walls looking for money!

02:33.905 --> 02:36.908
Only not so smart, maybe.

02:50.797 --> 02:52.965
How did you know money
was in fucking locker?

02:53.007 --> 02:54.509
I didn't, I don't know.

02:54.926 --> 02:55.843
I don't know.

03:01.307 --> 03:03.726
It was Constantine, yeah?

03:04.936 --> 03:06.854
Reggie just found a key.

03:08.272 --> 03:09.857
Reggie just found a key.

03:18.574 --> 03:23.788
Now, that is a shame, because Constantine,
he was good friend.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.378
Let's go, donkey.
We go get my fucking money.

03:30.461 --> 03:31.629
You, you can't.

03:33.715 --> 03:34.757
You... you can't.

03:36.008 --> 03:37.885
The Feds are still watching you.

03:37.927 --> 03:38.803
The...

03:40.388 --> 03:42.056
They wanted us to set you up.

03:42.724 --> 03:45.393
The Feds were talking to 'em
when Joe and I...

03:46.352 --> 03:47.395
When we grabbed 'em.

03:49.188 --> 03:50.189
Are they wired?

03:50.398 --> 03:52.358
No. We checked.

03:52.525 --> 03:54.819
What did you say to FBI?

03:55.695 --> 03:56.571
We said no.

03:57.613 --> 03:58.489
Why?

04:03.703 --> 04:06.706
Because she had a vision.

04:07.540 --> 04:11.085
The only way to get out of this was to
get the money and give it back to you.

04:13.880 --> 04:14.756
A vision?

04:15.256 --> 04:16.924
Yeah, she's some kind of psychic.

04:17.759 --> 04:18.634
Yeah?

04:20.928 --> 04:26.684
You know, in village where I grow up,
there was a woman who also...

04:26.726 --> 04:28.019
she had visions.

04:28.644 --> 04:35.610
She would read, uh, coffee grinds,
and she said she could see future.

04:36.652 --> 04:41.407
Only, do you know what
old woman did not see?

04:44.160 --> 04:45.161
War.

04:48.539 --> 04:52.585
War! 140,000 dead.

04:54.086 --> 04:56.839
Two million refugees.

04:57.465 --> 05:02.345
Not one premonition about decade of blood!

05:07.308 --> 05:08.935
Fucking gypsy horseshit.

05:10.770 --> 05:14.607
The... the Feds wanna catch you
with the money.

05:14.649 --> 05:17.902
They, uh, they...
they wanna get you on tax evasion.

05:19.862 --> 05:21.405
- Like Capone?
- That's right.

05:22.907 --> 05:27.245
So you, you can't go near your money
until it's safe to go near your money

05:27.662 --> 05:30.665
and we want to get it for you
and make it safe.

05:32.041 --> 05:32.917
OK.

05:34.126 --> 05:38.047
I give you 24 hours to figure out how.

05:39.423 --> 05:41.884
You fucking go with them.

05:42.260 --> 05:45.888
They fuck around at all, you remind them

05:47.223 --> 05:51.602
I get my money,
or entire family goes in fucking tub.

06:03.489 --> 06:05.533
- So Joe was your friend?
- Don't.

06:06.367 --> 06:07.827
You know, I've worked in grief therapy.

06:07.869 --> 06:12.123
Next fucking word out of your mouth
better be about where the money really is.

06:12.665 --> 06:14.458
Anything else, I throw you from this car.

06:15.459 --> 06:16.586
It's where I said.

06:16.919 --> 06:17.920
Fucking asshole.

06:18.421 --> 06:19.297
In a buffalo.

06:20.882 --> 06:22.383
- Yeah.
- When you started on that

06:23.217 --> 06:24.802
I thought you were going in the tub.

06:32.059 --> 06:34.228
That's why you stashed Pete at the casino

06:36.230 --> 06:37.648
so that he could watch the buffalo.

06:39.317 --> 06:41.944
I have to be the one
to give the money back to Luka.

06:42.695 --> 06:44.822
- According to your vision.
- Yes.

06:46.115 --> 06:47.241
How about you, Fake Pete?

06:48.492 --> 06:49.493
Do you have a vision?

06:53.623 --> 06:55.041
We're gonna need more operators.

06:55.917 --> 06:57.043
I'm thinking four.

06:57.418 --> 06:59.337
I could hire one locally, but, uh...

07:00.046 --> 07:02.590
I'm gonna have to go into the city tomorrow
to get the rest.

07:02.715 --> 07:05.927
We'll go to the city tomorrow.
You're not leaving my sight.

07:08.054 --> 07:09.597
And what about her? What does she do?

07:10.181 --> 07:12.058
I'll make a list of tools for her to get.

07:15.645 --> 07:18.189
At some point,
we're gonna have to open up a buffalo.

07:24.779 --> 07:27.156
♪ It's getting harder out here ♪

07:29.492 --> 07:32.662
♪ I keep tryin' to just make my way ♪

07:33.913 --> 07:35.164
♪ It's not lyin' ♪

07:38.125 --> 07:39.669
♪ I'm only tryin' ♪

07:43.130 --> 07:45.049
♪ Just trust in me ♪

07:45.591 --> 07:47.134
♪ Trust in me ♪

07:47.551 --> 07:49.470
♪ Just trust in me ♪

07:50.012 --> 07:51.722
♪ Trust in me ♪

07:52.014 --> 07:54.183
♪ Just trust in me. ♪

08:01.315 --> 08:03.609
You really think I'd give you
someone else's passport?

08:03.901 --> 08:04.902
Driver's license?

08:05.528 --> 08:07.363
What if I get carded at the liquor store?

08:12.326 --> 08:14.161
You're not leaving the house.
You do know that, right?

08:14.203 --> 08:16.580
I was kidding, obviously.

08:18.249 --> 08:19.250
Oh, God.

08:20.167 --> 08:21.043
How many weeks?

08:21.544 --> 08:25.881
Mm, 23? Puking just stopped, so, yay.

08:27.383 --> 08:30.553
Hey, did Luis tell you
why he was bonding me out?

08:30.886 --> 08:31.762
Said he owed you.

08:32.722 --> 08:35.099
Oh. For what he owes me,
I should be in the Four Seasons

08:35.141 --> 08:36.350
not stuck here with you.

08:37.268 --> 08:40.021
- No offense.
- I'd rather be home with my kids.

08:40.187 --> 08:41.063
I hear ya.

08:42.148 --> 08:44.233
I'll be in court on Monday.
I don't come out.

08:44.275 --> 08:45.901
End of the month, I'll be in Niantic.

08:46.569 --> 08:48.779
Just can't believe
I'm having a baby in prison.

08:50.031 --> 08:50.906
Father around?

08:51.574 --> 08:52.450
Mexico.

08:53.409 --> 08:54.910
Why you skipped before.

08:55.369 --> 08:56.328
Can you blame me?

08:59.915 --> 09:04.045
So what are we gonna do?
Braid each other's hair, play Truth or Dare?

09:04.503 --> 09:06.756
I figured you'd want to watch what you want

09:06.881 --> 09:08.841
eat what you want, sleep when you want.

09:08.966 --> 09:10.843
- Just without leaving your sight?
- That's right.

09:42.541 --> 09:43.417
Feds.

09:46.170 --> 09:47.505
Subtle as fuck.

09:50.466 --> 09:52.134
Hey, I'm gonna need you
to wait in the car for this.

09:52.176 --> 09:53.803
You haven't caught on yet.

09:55.513 --> 09:56.555
I don't trust you.

09:57.473 --> 09:59.892
In fact, I blame you
for what happened to Joe.

10:04.814 --> 10:05.815
Say it's on me

10:06.398 --> 10:07.942
you'll never make it out of this car.

10:08.234 --> 10:10.569
No, it's not on you, it's not on me.

10:10.611 --> 10:12.279
It's on the guy who threw the acid.

10:12.446 --> 10:15.407
No, it's you, same as if you threw it.

10:17.201 --> 10:18.577
And it's got to be paid for.

10:19.537 --> 10:20.579
Pay for it you will.

10:20.621 --> 10:24.750
Listen, the person that I need to recruit
is gonna run if she sees you.

10:25.793 --> 10:26.669
Is it Gina?

10:27.419 --> 10:28.921
- Yeah.
- Get someone else.

10:28.963 --> 10:29.839
No.

10:30.089 --> 10:33.175
She's young, she's pretty,
and she's good at what she does.

10:33.217 --> 10:35.386
It needs to be Gina.
That's all we have right now.

10:40.558 --> 10:41.433
Go ahead.

10:44.728 --> 10:48.232
Oh, my God, I love your watch.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.776
My dad has one just like it.

10:50.818 --> 10:51.777
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

10:51.819 --> 10:53.612
Thanks. My wife got it for me.

10:53.654 --> 10:55.114
- Oh!
- Well, my ex-wife, actually, I'm...

10:55.406 --> 10:56.282
I'm single.

10:56.574 --> 10:57.449
Aw.

10:57.575 --> 10:59.285
You can collect it at
the end of the counter.

11:00.161 --> 11:01.579
Right. Thanks.

11:03.998 --> 11:06.834
- Help the next--
- Coffee. Black coffee.

11:09.837 --> 11:11.964
- Can I talk to you for a few seconds?
- Why?

11:12.298 --> 11:13.299
Just give me ten seconds.

11:13.340 --> 11:15.718
If you don't like what I have to say,
then you'll never see me again.

11:20.848 --> 11:22.224
Just one second.

11:25.895 --> 11:26.854
Ten seconds.

11:28.898 --> 11:29.857
Five seconds.

11:30.274 --> 11:31.150
Listen.

11:33.235 --> 11:34.904
I need your help with this thing.

11:34.945 --> 11:35.821
I need you.

11:37.823 --> 11:38.782
Listen, listen.

11:42.912 --> 11:46.874
There's nothing...
there's nothing I can say about Gavin.

11:49.168 --> 11:51.545
I am, I am so sorry about that.

11:56.508 --> 11:59.845
I want you to be my partner on this thing.
You don't need me to teach you.

12:00.221 --> 12:01.680
I need you. I need your help.

12:01.722 --> 12:02.598
You're gifted.

12:06.435 --> 12:07.311
I need you.

12:15.819 --> 12:17.112
What's the timeline?

12:19.031 --> 12:20.074
It's accelerated.

12:20.115 --> 12:22.576
It's basically now.
I have to go out the back door.

12:22.618 --> 12:23.494
Why?

12:23.911 --> 12:25.788
You see that black Suburban outside?

12:27.498 --> 12:28.540
That's the FBI.

12:30.542 --> 12:32.294
Smart not to mention the Feds up front.

12:35.673 --> 12:36.799
There's another reason.

12:45.516 --> 12:46.850
Is that who I think it is?

12:46.892 --> 12:49.937
This is not just about
the money or the job.

12:51.855 --> 12:52.982
It's about revenge.

12:55.943 --> 12:56.944
Meet me out back.

13:02.825 --> 13:04.743
Otto.

13:05.369 --> 13:08.080
We don't see each other like we used to
back in the day, huh?

13:08.330 --> 13:12.543
Your guys have gotten smarter.
It's bad for the bail bond business, but...

13:13.210 --> 13:14.545
I just got better lawyers.

13:17.381 --> 13:18.966
So, you got my message?

13:20.551 --> 13:22.177
Your mess.. message? What message?

13:22.511 --> 13:23.804
The one I left with Julia.

13:24.138 --> 13:28.559
Oh, well, this is the first, uh,
first I'm hearing of it.

13:28.892 --> 13:32.563
I just wanted to ask you about
the housepainter I sent you through Moe.

13:35.065 --> 13:35.983
What?

13:36.317 --> 13:38.152
We're just talking
home improvements, right?

13:38.819 --> 13:39.695
Uh, yeah, right.

13:40.279 --> 13:42.948
I tried reaching him and nothing.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.243
Then this kid shows up, looking for him.

13:46.327 --> 13:47.202
Something happen?

13:48.996 --> 13:49.872
Ah, well...

13:51.373 --> 13:54.543
long and short of it
is he took an early retirement.

13:57.129 --> 13:58.005
Hm.

13:58.172 --> 14:01.091
His kid, you send him to Moe?

14:02.301 --> 14:04.511
- He the one that put him in a hospital?
- Uh-huh.

14:04.553 --> 14:05.429
Ah.

14:05.846 --> 14:07.473
His kid's the reason we're here.

14:08.432 --> 14:10.017
He didn't just bust Moe's jaw.

14:11.894 --> 14:16.315
He... he took something important from him

14:17.441 --> 14:18.317
and, uh...

14:19.318 --> 14:23.614
I was hoping that maybe
you could convince him to give it back.

14:25.491 --> 14:27.576
I'd love to, Otto,
but I don't know his name

14:27.785 --> 14:29.036
where he lives, nothing.

14:30.746 --> 14:31.622
Sorry.

14:32.623 --> 14:33.499
Yeah.

14:57.189 --> 14:58.065
Fuck.

15:05.739 --> 15:07.032
- Hi.
- Oh, God!

15:08.409 --> 15:11.161
- How're you feeling?
- I'm fine. Why?

15:11.703 --> 15:13.705
- You're not hungover?
- No.

15:15.165 --> 15:16.792
Ah, youth.

15:17.626 --> 15:20.170
- What are you doing?
- Um...

15:20.879 --> 15:22.089
I'm looking for this.

15:23.715 --> 15:24.591
A screwdriver?

15:25.592 --> 15:27.928
Yeah, well, uh,
you can read certain objects.

15:27.970 --> 15:30.764
You can feel the echoes of the person
who owned it before

15:30.806 --> 15:32.641
I mean, if it was important to them.

15:33.851 --> 15:34.977
This was your mum's.

15:36.395 --> 15:38.480
She had a special screwdriver?

15:38.522 --> 15:41.191
Well, yeah, she had an '85 Ford Bronco

15:41.233 --> 15:43.944
and, uh, one summer, the solenoid went out.

15:44.653 --> 15:46.447
- I don't know what that is.
- Yeah, neither did I

15:46.488 --> 15:48.657
but apparently,
you can't start a car without one.

15:48.699 --> 15:53.203
Anyway, this guy, he told Lila
that if you lay the shaft of a screwdriver

15:53.454 --> 15:57.749
across two points in the engine,
and you get a spark

15:57.791 --> 16:00.461
and it starts, but you're only supposed
to do that one time.

16:00.669 --> 16:02.379
And then you're supposed
to take it right to the shop

16:02.421 --> 16:05.466
but Lila, she did it all summer long.

16:06.133 --> 16:08.010
Are you gonna read the screwdriver?

16:08.051 --> 16:12.723
I mean, can you use that to contact my mum?

16:14.141 --> 16:15.184
That's why I'm here.

16:17.853 --> 16:20.147
- That kid's gonna kill someone.
- What?

16:20.856 --> 16:23.734
That piece of paper
he wanted to get out of his father's jacket

16:24.067 --> 16:27.404
dollars to doughnuts, it's got the name
of his father's next target.

16:27.446 --> 16:29.698
That could've been the receipt
for his dry cleaning for all you know.

16:29.740 --> 16:33.911
Look, I spent a day with the little prick!
Alright?

16:34.578 --> 16:35.913
I know.

16:36.079 --> 16:37.623
He wants to be like Daddy.

16:37.664 --> 16:40.083
What, uh... what business is that of yours?

16:41.418 --> 16:44.129
OK, look, we find him,
we get the Proclamation

16:44.171 --> 16:45.923
- and it's done, OK?
- OK.

16:45.964 --> 16:47.466
You happen to get his license plate?

16:47.508 --> 16:48.967
No, because I'm old and stupid.

16:49.009 --> 16:50.219
Of course I got his plate.

16:50.636 --> 16:51.970
Kid's gonna kill someone.

16:52.638 --> 16:55.682
Yeah, well,
maybe whoever it is deserves it.

16:55.724 --> 16:56.767
You ever think about that?

17:06.610 --> 17:08.070
Valerie Abeyta.

17:19.414 --> 17:20.624
Could you please stop doing that?

17:22.084 --> 17:22.960
Sorry.

17:29.174 --> 17:30.342
Tell me about your kids.

17:32.261 --> 17:34.179
- I'm interested.
- What do you want to know?

17:34.596 --> 17:35.472
How many?

17:35.889 --> 17:37.099
Two, girl and a boy.

17:37.558 --> 17:38.433
Nice.

17:39.268 --> 17:40.477
Where are they this weekend?

17:40.769 --> 17:42.980
With a sitter,
who I'm paying an arm and a leg.

17:43.814 --> 17:44.982
You a good mother?

17:48.527 --> 17:52.197
Depends, uh, what day it is and who you ask

17:52.406 --> 17:54.908
but... we do the best.

17:56.368 --> 17:59.246
I hope I'll be a good
mother when I get out.

18:00.706 --> 18:01.582
Any advice?

18:03.500 --> 18:04.710
Don't do it on your own.

18:05.544 --> 18:07.963
- Yeah, that ship's kinda sailed.
- Tell me about it.

18:10.215 --> 18:11.758
Look, the good outweighs the bad.

18:12.384 --> 18:14.595
You'll never love anyone
the way you love them

18:14.636 --> 18:17.472
so don't sweat the small stuff.

18:18.682 --> 18:21.059
And be prepared, because everyone thinks
they know how to raise your kids

18:21.101 --> 18:22.060
better than you do.

18:22.185 --> 18:23.729
Shit, they probably do.

18:23.937 --> 18:25.355
Some days it'll feel like that.

18:29.568 --> 18:30.444
Shit.

18:31.570 --> 18:33.697
Batteries must've drained
while I was in jail.

18:36.241 --> 18:37.117
Oy...

18:38.327 --> 18:39.411
What are their names?

18:39.870 --> 18:41.163
Ellen and Jacob.

18:42.080 --> 18:47.961
- Their father around?
- Uh... Well, Jacob's is, sort of.

18:48.420 --> 18:52.090
Ellen's dad is in New York, or was.

18:52.341 --> 18:56.803
- Uh-huh.
- He represents a... dark period in my life.

18:57.804 --> 19:00.390
Having Ellen sort of saved me.

19:22.788 --> 19:24.623
Motherfuck.

19:28.043 --> 19:29.044
No, no, no, no.

19:29.628 --> 19:30.629
Oh, no, no, no.

20:03.829 --> 20:05.580
Ah, fuck... come on.

20:13.130 --> 20:15.966
- You got a fucking problem, man?
- Holy shit.

20:16.007 --> 20:17.926
You're that fugitive, that guy on TV.

20:18.135 --> 20:19.428
- What? No, no, I...
- Yes!

20:19.469 --> 20:20.512
Security!

20:21.388 --> 20:22.806
Escaped convict!

20:23.974 --> 20:25.100
He's getting away!

20:28.687 --> 20:30.397
No, no, no, no!

20:35.360 --> 20:36.278
We got an hour.

20:56.047 --> 20:58.008
Shit, I'm such a klutz.

21:18.153 --> 21:20.655
Cookies or Christ, whatever you're selling,
I ain't buying

21:20.697 --> 21:21.823
so just please--
Where is she?

21:21.865 --> 21:24.075
- Where is who?
- Do not fuck with me.

21:24.117 --> 21:25.869
I don't know who you are,
but I'm calling the cops.

21:25.911 --> 21:28.288
Please do. I work with Bernhardt Bail Bonds

21:28.663 --> 21:30.332
and we bonded out your friend Valerie...

21:30.373 --> 21:32.250
- Who the hell is Valerie?
- ...giving me the legal right

21:32.292 --> 21:35.212
to search anywhere I think she
might be hiding, so call the cops

21:35.253 --> 21:38.048
cos when they get here and we find Valerie
hiding in the attic or the basement

21:38.089 --> 21:40.383
or under a bed,
you go away for five to seven

21:40.425 --> 21:41.593
for aiding and abetting.

21:46.807 --> 21:47.682
Hands!

21:48.809 --> 21:49.684
Alright.

21:54.231 --> 21:55.857
Valerie, Valerie, Valerie.

21:58.819 --> 22:00.195
How did you know I was here?

22:00.654 --> 22:02.948
Your magazines.
Half the labels were for this address.

