40:45.819 --> 40:47.696
Oh, you son of a bitch, Marius...

40:47.780 --> 40:48.656
What?

40:50.866 --> 40:51.867
I gotta get out of here.

40:51.909 --> 40:54.244
Until I understand what's going on,
you're not going anywhere.

40:54.578 --> 40:55.454
No, no.

40:56.580 --> 40:58.415
I know my rights, OK?

40:58.457 --> 41:01.961
Unless I'm under arrest
or you're gonna charge me with a crime

41:02.378 --> 41:03.587
you've gotta let me go.

41:03.629 --> 41:04.505
So, come on.

41:04.922 --> 41:06.173
Take the cuffs off. Come on.

41:11.595 --> 41:13.597
OK, yeah, yeah.

41:15.474 --> 41:18.602
If anybody gets close,
just tell 'em it's toxic within five feet.

41:27.486 --> 41:29.655
Hey, I was about to call you.

41:32.157 --> 41:33.242
Blood test come back?

41:33.867 --> 41:37.746
No, but my afternoon became free
so I came up to go through evidence again.

41:37.788 --> 41:40.749
Just spent a half hour going through
the garbage from Winslow's car.

41:40.791 --> 41:43.752
Found a piece of paper with some numbers
scrawled on it.

41:46.046 --> 41:48.090
- Phone number or...?
- Not enough digits.

41:49.299 --> 41:53.345
- An address?
- 39 27 15.

41:55.222 --> 41:56.306
Mean anything to you?

41:57.099 --> 41:58.058
No, I don't...

42:01.353 --> 42:05.441
General Tso's chicken, shrimp fried rice,
and a hot and sour soup.

42:08.068 --> 42:09.653
- Winslow's takeout order.
- Ah.

42:10.195 --> 42:12.531
- You cracked the case.
- Wide open.

42:12.573 --> 42:16.827
You know, I can understand why you wanted
to share this momentous moment with me.

42:17.119 --> 42:19.496
Well, actually, um, it just made me hungry

42:20.039 --> 42:23.167
and you seem to be the guy
who knows where to eat around here, so.

42:33.927 --> 42:35.387
Did you betray your friend?

42:38.891 --> 42:40.434
Ah, you'll say anything, won't ya?

42:40.476 --> 42:43.145
- If you don't wanna talk about it--
- You know I don't wanna talk about it

42:43.896 --> 42:45.355
and yet you asked the question.

42:47.024 --> 42:48.358
To what fucking end?

42:56.784 --> 43:01.371
Three months looking for you,
Luka comes to me.

43:04.666 --> 43:06.043
Says he doesn't trust Joe.

43:07.753 --> 43:10.714
I say, "Joe's a little hot-headed,
but he's smart."

43:13.175 --> 43:18.472
And Luka says give him a heads-up
if, you know, Joe's thinking anything.

43:18.764 --> 43:19.807
He'll pay me extra.

43:23.227 --> 43:26.396
I told him, "Joe's cool.
Keep your money."

43:29.650 --> 43:32.111
And a few days ago, he asks again.

43:34.947 --> 43:39.535
I say, "Joe's a little antsy,
but I can handle him."

43:43.330 --> 43:44.206
That's it.

43:47.000 --> 43:48.043
That's all I said.

43:52.339 --> 43:53.382
It's my father.

43:53.799 --> 43:54.758
On speaker.

43:56.927 --> 43:57.803
Hey, Dad.

43:58.053 --> 43:59.054
<i>Where are you?</i>

44:01.181 --> 44:03.725
Uh, just running an errand.

44:04.184 --> 44:07.563
- In the, uh, state of Connecticut?
- Yeah, Dad.

44:09.022 --> 44:10.274
Can you come for dinner?

44:10.983 --> 44:11.859
<i>Not tonight.</i>

44:13.110 --> 44:13.986
Tomorrow?

44:14.653 --> 44:17.322
Dad, have you discussed
this with Mum at all?

44:17.948 --> 44:20.909
Look, I do not need to run everything
by your mother.

44:21.368 --> 44:23.912
Oh, you almost sound convincing
when you said that.

44:24.121 --> 44:24.997
Did I?

44:25.914 --> 44:26.915
Well, I was trying.

44:27.332 --> 44:28.208
Yeah.

44:28.333 --> 44:31.128
<i>It's so good to have you back, pumpkin.</i>

44:32.045 --> 44:35.299
Best thing to happen in 20 years.

44:36.758 --> 44:37.843
For me, too, Dad.

44:39.136 --> 44:40.012
I love you.

44:40.846 --> 44:41.889
<i>Love you, too, Mags.</i>

44:42.764 --> 44:43.849
Call you tomorrow.

44:48.979 --> 44:50.731
You hadn't seen your fam in 20 years?

44:52.524 --> 44:53.400
Why?

44:53.775 --> 44:54.985
I don't know anymore.

44:59.198 --> 45:00.073
Boom.

45:01.992 --> 45:04.912
- You get it?
- I got to pay for a new crown.

45:04.953 --> 45:09.333
Cracked his tooth on a pistachio shell
but, yeah, I got it.

45:10.209 --> 45:11.960
According to the license plate...

45:12.002 --> 45:13.462
- There you go, Sammy.
- Thank you.

45:13.879 --> 45:16.715
Hitman's son is Colin McCann.

45:16.965 --> 45:19.968
Lives with his dad, the late David McCann

45:20.010 --> 45:22.346
at 2574 Beachwood.

45:31.855 --> 45:32.731
Oh!

45:34.399 --> 45:36.985
Don't, don't come in here!
You're inhaling the fumes!

45:37.236 --> 45:38.904
You have to come out of the tent.

45:39.446 --> 45:40.656
Let's go, now.

45:41.406 --> 45:45.494
OK, I'm sorry. I'm in the middle
of a very delicate procedure here and I...

45:49.373 --> 45:50.832
Is there something you want to tell me?

45:50.874 --> 45:52.334
What did she say to you?

45:52.834 --> 45:54.795
I told her you're a con artist.

45:55.045 --> 45:56.421
Oh, really? Really?

45:56.463 --> 45:57.673
OK, what else did she say?

45:58.048 --> 46:00.384
She said you're trying
to steal the buffalo.

46:00.425 --> 46:02.552
Does it look like I'm trying to steal
the buffalo or does it look like I'm trying

46:02.594 --> 46:06.848
- to save a priceless piece of Americana?
- Ask him if he has any credentials.

46:07.140 --> 46:09.184
Of course I have ATA accreditation.

46:09.226 --> 46:11.937
I-I-I don't have it on me,
because it's all electronic now.

46:11.979 --> 46:15.148
- What are you doing here, Andrea?
- My name's not Andrea.

46:15.190 --> 46:17.567
Can I talk to you for a second?
Can I just talk to you for one second

46:17.609 --> 46:19.194
over here? No. No, no!

46:19.236 --> 46:21.822
I'm gonna... I'm gonna talk to her
in private, you fucking stalker.

46:21.863 --> 46:22.864
Not you. I'm sorry.

46:22.990 --> 46:24.574
Can I just talk to you for one second?

46:24.616 --> 46:28.495
Look, I don't... I don't know
what her driver's license says

46:28.537 --> 46:31.957
but her name's Andrea Little,
and obviously we have a history.

46:32.249 --> 46:34.293
Let's just say, though,
I left her at the altar

46:34.334 --> 46:38.797
only the altar this time was the locked
ward at the Marienbad Psychiatric Facility

46:38.839 --> 46:40.674
in Baden-Baden, Germany.
Oh, yeah.

46:40.716 --> 46:42.926
Two days before we were gonna tie the knot

46:42.968 --> 46:46.930
I found out she was clinically insane
and that everything she told me was a lie.

46:47.139 --> 46:51.059
And ever since she got out, she's been
trying to systematically ruin my life.

46:51.101 --> 46:52.144
- Gina? Gina...
- Yes.

46:52.185 --> 46:56.189
Tell Suzanne how Crazy Andrea has been
trying to make our lives miserable.

46:56.315 --> 46:58.859
I thought we weren't gonna use words
like "crazy" anymore.

46:58.900 --> 47:01.570
- I know, I know. Look at my hand, I'm shaking.
- I know, baby, I'm sorry.

47:01.611 --> 47:04.573
She is better when she's under
a physician's care, but when she's not

47:05.157 --> 47:06.992
there have been times
we've been afraid for our lives.

47:07.075 --> 47:10.078
No, you need to call security
and take her someplace safe

47:10.120 --> 47:11.580
and then I'll finish the buffalo.

47:12.039 --> 47:13.915
She said I shouldn't believe
anything you said.

47:13.957 --> 47:15.792
Of course she did. Classic projection.

47:15.876 --> 47:17.294
You know what? I'm gonna, I...

47:17.336 --> 47:20.047
I'm gonna talk to her for one second.
I'm gonna get Dr Zeltzer on the phone

47:20.088 --> 47:21.506
and then, then hopefully
I'll finish the buffalo.

47:21.548 --> 47:22.424
OK, but...

47:23.925 --> 47:25.260
Is it really a famous buffalo?

47:26.636 --> 47:27.804
I don't know.

47:28.305 --> 47:29.514
May I make a suggestion?

47:30.140 --> 47:31.183
Yes, Kwahu.

47:32.476 --> 47:36.188
Seeing as this is our slow season,
maybe there's another way to go at this.

47:38.440 --> 47:41.485
I... I talked to this homeless guy today.

47:42.986 --> 47:45.072
And, uh... Mmm.

47:45.781 --> 47:46.656
Good.

47:46.698 --> 47:47.657
There we go, hm?

47:48.617 --> 47:52.120
He seemed like such a smart guy, you know?

47:52.245 --> 47:53.497
Sharp, sense of humour.

47:55.082 --> 47:56.583
Could've been anything.
Could've been a... Here.

47:58.668 --> 48:00.087
A teacher or accountant.

48:01.588 --> 48:02.631
Or a cop?

48:04.466 --> 48:05.634
I was gonna say detective.

48:10.222 --> 48:13.600
Point is, he was a really regular guy,
you know?

48:13.642 --> 48:17.229
And I couldn't help think,
"What the hell happened?", you know?

48:17.979 --> 48:19.356
What went wrong for this guy?

48:20.690 --> 48:21.566
Mmm.

48:24.236 --> 48:25.112
Well...

48:26.905 --> 48:28.782
yeah, I mean, if a guy like that...

48:29.491 --> 48:31.201
if it can happen to him
then it could...

48:32.285 --> 48:33.537
really happen to any of us.

48:35.455 --> 48:36.498
Happen to you

48:37.416 --> 48:38.375
maybe even me.

48:39.167 --> 48:40.252
Probably not you.

48:45.173 --> 48:49.177
I think the road to hell is paved
with a million small bad choices.

48:50.262 --> 48:52.514
People still think that if they can find
the one wrong decision

48:52.556 --> 48:55.016
that's responsible for
all their bad luck...

49:02.607 --> 49:03.817
It just get cold out here?

49:03.984 --> 49:07.154
No, it was... family business rival.

49:07.195 --> 49:08.321
The guy's a total dick.

49:13.785 --> 49:15.745
He's certainly punching above
his weight class.

49:18.498 --> 49:19.541
So that's who it is.

49:21.543 --> 49:22.419
What?

49:23.044 --> 49:24.004
Who Bowman's fucking.

49:24.212 --> 49:25.839
Some NYPD detective.

49:25.881 --> 49:28.467
The guys at the station
say they've been together all week.

49:28.508 --> 49:31.553
Now he takes her out for what I
guess for him is a lavish meal.

49:37.142 --> 49:38.351
- God!
- The fuck was that about?

49:38.393 --> 49:41.855
Yeah, well, I could ask you the same thing,
except I know what you were doing.

49:41.897 --> 49:44.232
- You were trying to steal the money.
- Of course I was.

49:44.274 --> 49:45.650
That's our fucking job.

49:45.692 --> 49:47.527
Yeah, well, you're trying to
steal the money for yourself.

49:47.569 --> 49:49.446
- No, I wasn't.
- You said you were in New York.

49:49.654 --> 49:51.114
- When we were on the phone!
- Yeah.

49:51.156 --> 49:52.407
I thought the FBI were listening.

49:52.449 --> 49:54.159
Earlier, you said that's where
you were going.

49:54.201 --> 49:56.912
I told you I was trying to crew up.
I came here to suss it out.

49:56.953 --> 49:59.706
I saw an opportunity, I took it.
I-I called you five times.

49:59.748 --> 50:01.958
- Oh, yeah, when? When?
- A couple hours ago.

50:02.000 --> 50:05.212
- OK, let me see your phone.
- I... the fucking phone is in the car.

50:05.253 --> 50:07.631
Listen, we still have a chance here.
We gotta go, come on!

50:07.672 --> 50:10.759
I thought that you cared about the family,
about Julia.

50:11.051 --> 50:13.053
I mean, maybe not me, but Carly?

50:13.261 --> 50:16.097
What happens when Luka
dissolves Carly in acid?

50:16.598 --> 50:18.767
- Say what, now?
- Yeah, he hasn't told you?

50:18.808 --> 50:21.853
Luka is threatening to kill us all
if he doesn't get his money.

50:22.270 --> 50:23.438
The people on the farm?

50:24.856 --> 50:27.484
I thought all that "never get
attached" talk was just a pose.

50:27.526 --> 50:28.944
- Listen, the family...
- That's cold.

50:28.985 --> 50:31.238
...is not in danger, I was gonna get
the money and give it to Luka.

50:31.279 --> 50:32.572
We can't give Luka the money.

50:32.948 --> 50:35.367
- What do you mean we can't give him the money?
- We can't give him the money.

50:35.408 --> 50:38.411
- What do you mean? What about your vision?
- My vision changed

50:38.578 --> 50:40.997
the second I saw the acid
hit that guy's face.

50:41.039 --> 50:43.208
- Someone's face?
- So now you have a new vision?

50:43.250 --> 50:44.834
- Yes.
- You have a new vision?

50:44.876 --> 50:47.379
But in this vision,
we get to keep the money.

50:47.629 --> 50:48.547
Hey!

50:50.048 --> 50:51.925
- Oh, God.
- What the fuck is he doing here?

50:51.967 --> 50:54.761
Look, it was either bring him
or Julia dies, OK?

50:55.053 --> 50:56.429
You were supposed to bring him outside.

50:56.721 --> 50:58.640
- I-I tried, Frank.
- Wow, hi.

50:58.682 --> 51:00.517
- Why don't we take a walk together, huh?
- No, no, don't.

51:00.559 --> 51:02.227
- Feel like we've been here before.
- You said that you wouldn't hurt him, Frank.

51:02.269 --> 51:03.770
I'm a bad guy. I lie.

51:03.812 --> 51:04.729
Mum!

51:11.695 --> 51:12.571
Hey, Ma.

51:15.156 --> 51:16.032
Pete, I'm...

51:19.035 --> 51:20.203
Hi. Oh, my God.

51:20.245 --> 51:21.788
- You look older.
- Oh.

51:22.330 --> 51:23.206
You don't.

51:27.210 --> 51:28.503
Give me one second, OK?

51:30.130 --> 51:31.006
Marius.

51:31.172 --> 51:32.632
Pete! How you doin'?

51:34.593 --> 51:36.595
That's for making me
think I was a fugitive.

51:36.636 --> 51:37.721
- Stop it!
- Asshole.

51:39.097 --> 51:39.973
Who are you?

51:42.434 --> 51:43.310
OK.

51:46.354 --> 51:47.230
Listen.

51:48.565 --> 51:49.441
Listen...

51:49.733 --> 51:51.568
we all want the money, right?

51:51.610 --> 51:57.365
The fumigation con isn't dead yet,
so let's just go get the fucking money.

51:57.657 --> 51:59.326
Kwahu says we have to go to the casino.

51:59.367 --> 52:00.493
Who the fuck is Kwahu?

52:00.535 --> 52:02.454
- He's been watching the buffalo.
- What?

52:02.495 --> 52:04.080
You think I was the only one?

52:04.122 --> 52:06.124
Yeah, he's the one who told me
what you were doing.

52:06.166 --> 52:08.710
- Not so smart now, huh, Marius?
- Wait, did he say museum or casino?

52:08.752 --> 52:09.711
He said casino.

52:11.755 --> 52:13.340
Wait!

52:23.850 --> 52:26.269
Aright, so the three of us
are gonna be banned from the casino.

52:26.519 --> 52:28.229
You can't be seen with us. Wait over there.

52:28.271 --> 52:29.230
Go, go, go.

52:34.194 --> 52:35.070
Suzanne.

52:36.154 --> 52:39.574
Hey, I'm sorry about that.
Uh, Andrea's calmed down.

52:39.616 --> 52:40.492
Sorry about that.

52:41.159 --> 52:42.702
I'm gonna have to ask
the three of you to leave.

52:42.744 --> 52:44.913
Right, but, you know,
we were in the middle of the fumigation.

52:44.954 --> 52:47.332
The buffalo really should be secluded
because of the toxicity.

52:47.374 --> 52:48.583
Don't make me get security.

52:50.126 --> 52:52.128
Oh, is that how it's gonna be? Really?

52:52.295 --> 52:55.423
OK, so, when the buffalo's corpuscles
explode all over the place

52:55.465 --> 52:57.342
that's gonna be on you, literally.

52:58.385 --> 52:59.886
Come on, Gina. Come on, Andrea.

52:59.928 --> 53:01.012
But my name is not...

53:07.018 --> 53:10.730
It's in the middle of a casino,
surrounded by 24-hour security.

53:11.022 --> 53:12.273
How do we get to it now?

53:13.483 --> 53:15.902
If David Copperfield can make
the Statue of Liberty disappear

53:15.944 --> 53:17.946
we can vanish a buffalo from a casino.
